  "text": "In our study, we selected a protocol that implemented infra-slow EEG frequencies (below 0.1 Hz) as a biofeedback parameter in three depressed individuals. The time course of the signal at these very slow frequencies reflects variations in cortical excitability [CITATION_1] van Putten, Tjepkema-Cloostermans, & Hofmeijer, 2014) . This suggests that the most direct effect of the neurofeedback challenge is on the regulation of tonic central arousal. The within-session effects of perceived calming are consistent with this hypothesis.",
